Global Prosecco Market Insights
Prosecco Market size was valued at USD 4.03 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 7.17 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 8.3% from 2024 to 2030.

Prosecco Market Overview
The global Prosecco market has experienced significant growth in recent years, with a market value of approximately USD 5.5 billion in 2024 and a projected CAGR of 8.5% from 2024 to 2030. This growth is driven by the increasing preference for sparkling wines and Prosecco's rising popularity among younger consumers. The market is mainly concentrated in Europe, particularly Italy, where Prosecco is a national favorite, and North America, where demand is also expanding due to shifting consumer preferences. The premiumization trend in the wine sector has contributed to an increased willingness among consumers to spend on high-quality sparkling wines like Prosecco, further boosting market demand.

